Reading in Cockle Data csv

CockleData <- read.csv("../data/CockleData.csv")

Kruskal-Wallis one-way analysis of variance analyzing female gonad grade by date

kruskal.test(CockleData$`Female.Gonad.Grade`~CockleData$Date)
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  CockleData$Female.Gonad.Grade by CockleData$Date
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 3.6567, df = 3, p-value = 0.301

Kruskal-Wallis one-way analysis of variance analyzing male gonad grade by date

kruskal.test(CockleData$`Male.Grade`~CockleData$Date)
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  CockleData$Male.Grade by CockleData$Date
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 3.3918, df = 3, p-value = 0.3351

Ordered Logistic Regression of female gonad grade analyzed by width and height

summary(polr(as.factor(CockleData$`Female.Gonad.Grade`)~CockleData$`Width..cm.`+CockleData$`Height..cm.`,Hess=TRUE))
## Call:
## polr(formula = as.factor(CockleData$Female.Gonad.Grade) ~ CockleData$Width..cm. + 
##     CockleData$Height..cm., Hess = TRUE)
## 
## Coefficients:
##                         Value Std. Error t value
## CockleData$Width..cm.   1.825      1.039   1.755
## CockleData$Height..cm. -1.425      1.082  -1.317
## 
## Intercepts:
##                                 Value   Std. Error t value
## 1- Underdeveloped|2- Developing  0.0761  1.1650     0.0653
## 2- Developing|3- Developed       2.7318  1.2614     2.1656
## 
## Residual Deviance: 66.12909 
## AIC: 74.12909
ctableF <-coef(summary(polr(as.factor(CockleData$`Female.Gonad.Grade`)~CockleData$`Width..cm.`+ CockleData$`Height..cm.`,Hess=TRUE)))

p <- pnorm(abs(ctableF[, "t value"]), lower.tail = FALSE) * 2

(ctableF <- cbind(ctableF, "p value" =p))
##                                       Value Std. Error     t value    p value
## CockleData$Width..cm.            1.82456340   1.039368  1.75545494 0.07918152
## CockleData$Height..cm.          -1.42492817   1.081619 -1.31740339 0.18770345
## 1- Underdeveloped|2- Developing  0.07611703   1.164958  0.06533886 0.94790420

Making Plots

Figure 7. Date, male and female gonad stage, and width of each basket cockle 
ggplot(CockleData, aes(x=`Female.Gonad.Stage`, y=`Male.Gonad.Stage`, color=`Width..cm.`)) +geom_point()+facet_wrap(~Date)+geom_jitter(size=4, width =0.3, height =0.5)+xlab("Female Gonad Stage")+ylab("Male Gonad Stage")+labs(color="Width (cm)")+scale_color_gradient(low="navajowhite1",high="red3")+ theme(strip.background = element_rect( fill="white"),panel.background = element_rect(fill="white"),panel.grid.major = element_line("gray92"),panel.grid.minor = element_line("gray92"),panel.border = element_rect("black",size=0.5,fill=NA), strip.text=element_text(size=10))

Figure 9. Date, male and female gonad stage, and predicted age of each basket cockle
ggplot(CockleData, aes(x=`Female.Gonad.Stage`, y=`Male.Gonad.Stage`, color=`Predicted.Age`)) +geom_point()+facet_wrap(~Date)+geom_jitter(size=4, width =0.3, height =0.5)+xlab("Female Gonad Stage")+ylab("Male Gonad Stage")+labs(color="Predicted Age")+theme(strip.background = element_rect( fill="white"),panel.background = element_rect(fill="white"), panel.grid.major = element_line("gray92"), panel.grid.minor = element_line("gray92"),
panel.border = element_rect("black",size=0.5,fill=NA),strip.text=element_text(size=10)) + scale_colour_brewer(palette="RdYlBu")

SizeRange_FemaleGrade <- read.csv("../data/SizeRange_FemaleGrade.csv")

ggplot(SizeRange_FemaleGrade, aes(fill=Grade, x=`Width.range..cm.`,y=`Number.of.C..nuttallii`))+xlab("Width Range (cm)")+ylab("Number of C. nuttallii")+geom_bar(stat="identity")+scale_fill_brewer(palette="Oranges")+theme_bw()+theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
panel.grid.minor = element_blank())
